b'[<p><i><b>UFC Fight Night: Bader vs. Saint Preux</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC Fight Night 47</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held on August 16, 2014, at the <a href="/wiki/Cross_Insurance_Center" title="Cross Insurance Center">Cross Insurance Center</a> in <a href="/wiki/Bangor,_Maine" title="Bangor, Maine">Bangor, Maine</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-2"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The event was headlined by top ten light heavyweights <a href="/wiki/Ryan_Bader" title="Ryan Bader">Ryan Bader</a> and <a href="/wiki/Ovince_Saint_Preux" title="Ovince Saint Preux">Ovince Saint Preux</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The event was the first hosted in Maine.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-6"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-7"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>As a result of the cancellation of <a href="/wiki/UFC_176" title="UFC 176">UFC 176</a>, bouts between <a href="/wiki/Bobby_Green_(fighter)" title="Bobby Green (fighter)">Bobby Green</a> vs. <a href="/wiki/Abel_Trujillo" title="Abel Trujillo">Abel Trujillo</a>, <a href="/wiki/Jussier_Formiga" title="Jussier Formiga">Jussier Formiga</a> vs. <a href="/wiki/Zach_Makovsky" title="Zach Makovsky">Zach Makovsky</a><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-FN47_8-0"><a href="#cite_note-FN47-8">[8]</a></sup> and <a href="/wiki/Gray_Maynard" title="Gray Maynard">Gray Maynard</a> vs. <a href="/wiki/Fabr%C3%ADcio_Cam%C3%B5es" title="Fabr\xc3\xadcio Cam\xc3\xb5es">Fabr\xc3\xadcio Cam\xc3\xb5es</a> were rescheduled for this event.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-9"><a href="#cite_note-9">[9]</a></sup>  Subsequently, Green was removed from his fight on July 11 in favor of a bout as an injury replacement for <a href="/wiki/Michael_Johnson_(fighter)" title="Michael Johnson (fighter)">Michael Johnson</a> against <a href="/wiki/Josh_Thomson" title="Josh Thomson">Josh Thomson</a> at <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_on_Fox_12" title="UFC on Fox 12">UFC on Fox 12</a> on July 26, 2014.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-10"><a href="#cite_note-10">[10]</a></sup> Trujillo was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Ross_Pearson" title="Ross Pearson">Ross Pearson</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-11"><a href="#cite_note-11">[11]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>On August 4, Trujillo pulled out of the Pearson bout and was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Gray_Maynard" title="Gray Maynard">Gray Maynard</a>.  In turn, Maynard\'s originally scheduled opponent <a href="/wiki/Fabr%C3%ADcio_Cam%C3%B5es" title="Fabr\xc3\xadcio Cam\xc3\xb5es">Fabr\xc3\xadcio Cam\xc3\xb5es</a> was removed from the card entirely and was rebooked for a separate event with a new opponent.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-12"><a href="#cite_note-12">[12]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-13"><a href="#cite_note-13">[13]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following fighters were awarded $50,000 bonuses:<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-14"><a href="#cite_note-14">[14]</a></sup>\n</p>]'